HEADWORD: Gentleness
<hw>Gen"tle*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
gentle, well-born, mild, benevolent, docile, etc.; gentility; softness
of manners, disposition, etc.; mildness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

